4 HR____ COMMENDING SHERYL THREADGILL FOR 33 YEARS OF
5 EXTRAORDINARY SERVICE TO THE YOUTH OF WILCOX COUNTY.
6
7 WHEREAS, we take great pride and pleasure in
8 commending Sheryl Threadgill for extraordinary service to
9 the youth of Wilcox County; and
10 WHEREAS, Sheryl Threadgill has devoted more than
11 three decades to improving the lives of young people in
12 Wilcox County, demonstrating an unwavering commitment to
13 education, opportunity, and community development; and
14 WHEREAS, as Executive Director and driving force
15 behind the BAMA Kids program "Better Activities to Make
16 All-around Kids," she has helped provide academic support,
17 cultural enrichment, and character-building opportunities
18 for children throughout the region, particularly in reading,
19 grammar, and STEM education; and
20 WHEREAS, through programs such as arts excursions,
21 Kwanzaa celebrations, and community cultural events, her
22 leadership has fostered confidence, creativity, and civic
23 pride among thousands of young people who have benefited
24 from her vision and dedication; and
25 WHEREAS, motivated by a desire to provide
26 constructive opportunities for youth in her community, Ms.
27 Threadgill helped establish a program that has served
28 generations of children and continues to be a vital resource
Page 1

generations of children and continues to be a vital resource
HR147 INTRODUCED
29 in Wilcox County; and
30 WHEREAS, her career of service, which included work
31 in human services and community development, reflects a
32 lifelong commitment to strengthening families, empowering
33 youth, and improving quality of life throughout her
34 community and surrounding areas; and
35 WHEREAS, Sheryl Threadgill's legacy is reflected not
36 only in programs created but in the lives transformed, as
37 former participants continue to testify to the lasting
38 impact of her guidance and encouragement; now therefore,
39 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
40 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That we hereby commend Sheryl
41 Threadgill for 33 years of exemplary service to the youth of
42 Wilcox County and extend our sincere gratitude for her
43 leadership, dedication, and lasting contributions to her
44 community.
